{"input": {"source_code": "@SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\npublic static Map<String, String> deserializeOffsetMap(String lastSourceOffset) throws IOException {\n  Map<String, String> offsetMap;\n  if (lastSourceOffset == null || lastSourceOffset.isEmpty()) {    \n    offsetMap = new HashMap<>();  \n  } else {\n    offsetMap = JSON_MAPPER.readValue(lastSourceOffset, Map.class);  \n  }\n  return offsetMap;\n}\n", "repo_info": {"repo": "streamsets/datacollector", "path": "stagesupport/src/main/java/com/.../OffsetUtil.java", "function_name": "OffsetUtil.deserializeOffsetMap"}}, "output": "The provided code is a static method named `deserializeOffsetMap` in the Java class located at `stagesupport/src/main/java/com/.../OffsetUtil.java`. This method takes a single parameter: `lastSourceOffset`, which is of type `String`.\n\nHere's an explanation of what this method does:\n\n1. The method uses the `@SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")` annotation to suppress unchecked warnings, indicating that it is aware of potential issues with casting.\n\n2. It declares a variable named `offsetMap` of type `Map<String, String>`. This map will store key-value pairs where both keys and values are strings.\n\n3. The method checks if the `lastSourceOffset` parameter is either null or an empty string using the condition `if (lastSourceOffset == null || lastSourceOffset.isEmpty())`.\n\n4. If the `lastSourceOffset` is null or an empty string, it initializes a new instance of `HashMap<String, String>` and assigns it to the `offsetMap` variable.\n\n5. If the `lastSourceOffset` is not null or an empty string, it uses the `JSON_MAPPER` object (presumably an instance of Jackson's ObjectMapper) to deserialize the JSON string into a generic `Map` object using the `readValue` method. The deserialized map is then assigned to the `offsetMap` variable.\n\n6. Finally, the method returns the `offsetMap`.\n\nIn summary, this method takes a JSON-formatted string (`lastSourceOffset`) and attempts to deserialize it into a `HashMap<String, String>`. If the input string is null or empty, an empty map is returned instead.", "metric": 0.2536715620827771}
